Legs with many setae; length of I>III>IV>II, tibia I with 23 articles, tarsus I with 37 articles. Leg IV, basitibia : divided into 2 pseudo-articles, one trichobothria on the first pseudo-article, and one at the last one; distitibia: 3 basal trichobothria and 13 distal ( sf with 5 trichobothria, s c with 5 , and the 3 terminal ( tf , tm and tc ) (
Figure 2
). Basitibia-distitibia length : BT 1 >DT>BT 2 ; distitarsus tetramerous. Genitalia: Posterior margin of the genital operculum rounded with few setae. Female gonopods rounded, sucker-like and small. Without finger like appendage and with few setae along its posterior edge.

Color: alive: Cephalothorax and pedipalps: brownish with chelicerae and the tip of the pedipalp spines reddish. Legs: brownish with lighter articulations. Abdomen: dark-brown, with apical black stripe. Ethanol: same colors than alive but fader (
Figure 3
).
